etions) and broadcast to other connected users viewing the same document.\\n    18→\\n    19→3. **Conflict resolution** -- When two users edit simultaneously, their changes must not corrupt the document. Use Operational Transform (OT) or CRDTs to ensure all clients converge to the same document state. Both insertions must be preserved; nothing should be silently dropped.\\n    20→\\n    21→4. **Persistence** -- Use SQLite (via better-sqlite3) to persist documents and their version history. Data should survive server restarts.\\n    22→\\n    23→5. **Robustness** -- Handle at least 10 concurrent clients on the same document without corruption. Reject malformed or invalid operations gracefully (send error messages back, don't crash).\\n    24→\\n    25→## Structural Requirement\\n    26→\\n    27→Your server entry point must export a `createApp` factory function from `src/server.ts` (or `src/index.ts`). This function should accept an optional database file path and return an object with at least:\\n    28→\\n    29→- `app` -- the HTTP server/application (e.g., Express app)\\n    30→- `start(port?)` -- starts listening, returns the port number (use port 0 for a random available port)\\n    31→- `stop()` -- cleanly shuts down the server and all connections\\n    32→\\n    33→## Tech Stack\\n    34→\\n    35→- TypeScript (the project is already configured with tsconfig.json)\\n    36→- Express for HTTP\\n    37→- ws for WebSocket\\n    38→- better-sqlite3 for SQLite\\n    39→- All dependencies are pre-installed\\n    40→\\n    41→## What Success Looks Like\\n    42→\\n    43→- `npm run build` compiles without errors\\n    44→- `npm run lint` passes\\n    45→- The server handles the full lifecycle: create doc via REST, connect via WebSocket, send edits, receive broadcasts, verify convergence via REST\\n    46→- Documents persist across server restarts\\n    47→- Concurrent edits from multiple clients converge to consistent state\\n    48→\\n    49→## Tips\\n    50→\\n    51→- The WebSocket connection path should include the document ID so the server knows which document the client wants to collaborate on\\n    52→- Send a sync message with the current document content when a client first connects\\n    53→- Track document versions so you can transform concurrent operations correctly\\n    54→- Write tests for your implementation -- they'll help you catch edge cases\\n    55→\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01C4qpANL1643g4QjXADRjb2\",\"session_id\":\"9b5fd8e0-b085-4ec4-b9ca-d397d9662f3c\",\"uuid\":\"b6f14f0a-f0ba-4602-b0ab-d135ab9f937c\"}\n    24→{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01CJZbRXY36Ld1KfaZBPfMgG\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01E4gJkaRQUMoYCZbWmEvp7H\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/workspace/schema.sql\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":7,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1247,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":10486,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1247},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01C4qpANL1643g4QjXADRjb2\",\"session_id\":\"9b5fd8e0-b085-4ec4-b9ca-d397d9662f3c\",\"uuid\":\"008d5ba3-80bb-43ae-bf45-66b553bb5dad\"}\n    25→{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01E4gJkaRQUMoYCZbWmEvp7H\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS documents (\\n     2→  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\n     3→  title TEXT NOT NULL,\\n     4→  content TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\\n     5→  created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\\n     6→  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\\n     7→);\\n     8→\\n     9→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS versions (\\n    10→  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\\n    11→  document_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES documents(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\\n    12→  version INTEGER NOT NULL,\\n    13→  content TEXT NOT NULL,\\n    14→  operation TEXT, -- JSON of the operation that produced this version\\n    15→  created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\\n    16→  UNIQUE(document_id, version)\\n    17→);\\n    18→\\n    19→CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS active_connections (\\n    20→  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\\n    21→  document_id TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES documents(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\\n    22→  connected_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\\n    23→);\\n    24→\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01C4qpANL1643g4QjXADRjb2\",\"session_id\":\"9b5fd8e0-b085-4ec4-b9ca-d397d9662f3c\",\"uuid\":\"88a8ee85-d48e-47fc-b60f-28b6574abd63\"}\n    26→{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01CJZbRXY36Ld1KfaZBPfMgG\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01CZUZctk6mSPLJaAjf5vnz1\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/workspace/.gitignore\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":7,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1247,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":10486,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1247},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01C4qpANL1643g4QjXADRjb2\",\"session_id\":\"9b5fd8e0-b085-4ec4-b9ca-d397d9662f3c\",\"uuid\":\"dc388f04-8415-4a5d-a077-e5c6685899f6\"}\n    27→{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01CZUZctk6mSPLJaAjf5vnz1\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→node_modules/\\n     2→dist/\\n     3→*.db\\n     4→*.sqlite\\n     5→\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01C4qpANL1643g4QjXADRjb2\",\"session_id\":\"9b5fd8e0-b085-4ec4-b9ca-